<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Sexual state</emphasis>
not observed. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Conidiophores</emphasis>
macronematous, synnematous, 450-550 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
including conidiogenous apparatus, synnemata occasionally slightly swollen at the base, wider at the stipe, black to brown, expanding branches at the apex, light brown to hyaline, (25
<normalizedToken originalValue="–)39–44(–">-)39-44(-</normalizedToken>
50) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in width. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Conidiogenous cells</emphasis>
discrete, terminal, percurrent and phialidic proliferation, hyaline, cylindrical, (11
<normalizedToken originalValue="–)15–18(–">-)15-18(-</normalizedToken>
19) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Conidia</emphasis>
hyaline, one-celled, cylindrical to obovoid, (3.9
<normalizedToken originalValue="–)4.2–4.5(–">-)4.2-4.5(-</normalizedToken>
4.8) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.8-2.4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Cultural characteristics</emphasis>
: Colonies on OA, spore drops hyaline at first, later becoming light to dark yellowish in the center, hyphae hyaline, appressed and immersed, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">synnemata</emphasis>
predominant, aerial mycelium occasionally present on wood tissue, Optimal growth temperature on MEA is 25 °C with radial growth rate 2.0 (
<normalizedToken originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.5) mm/d, growth reduced at 10 °C, no growth at 30 °C.
</paragraph>
