<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
This species groups closely with 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. conplurium" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="conplurium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. conplurium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. erubescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="erubescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. erubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by its dark conidial droplets. In addition, the synnematous conidiophores of this species were shorter, and its conidia were bigger than that of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. erubescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="erubescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. erubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
